# 3.1.1.research.external.q2.apiKeyHelper-scope

## question

when does claude cli's `apiKeyHelper` get invoked?

## options

- on every request (hot path)
- only on startup (cold path)
- only when token is absent or expired
- on TTL interval
- on specific error codes

## why it matters

determines if we can inject via env var dynamically or need restart. critical for rotation mechanism.

## research approach

read claude cli source code, search for `apiKeyHelper` usage, check docs.

## .status

awaited
